[1]
Date: Mon, 22 Jan 2007
From: Magda Oneill <OneillM@arc.agric.za>

In the ongoing debate regarding the origin of the
European BTV 8, we would like to make the following comments.
We have amplified the complete genomes of all 16
South African BTV vaccine strains and partially
sequenced the VP2 segments (published). We have
completed the nucleotide sequencing of the VP2
segments of all vaccine strains (serotypes 1-14,
16 and 19) and the remaining reference strains
(manuscript in preparation). From this study we
can confirm what was said by Prof. Mertens about
the relatedness of the BTV 8 vaccine and
reference strains. These strains have almost
identical nucleotide sequences and dsRNA PAGE
profiles. [For Prof Mertens' views, see section
2 in "Bluetongue - Netherlands, Belgium, Germany
(08): BTV-8 origin 20060915.2615". - ModAS]
In a recent study we have also amplified the
complete genomes of more than 130 South African
BTV isolates (multiple serotypes) from 1986 to
2003. We have partially sequenced the VP2
segments and have identified 8 vaccine and 4 BTV
8 isolates. Therefore we have some sequence information on "western" BTV8.
Following the news of the European outbreak we
have prepared our BTV 8 virus isolates as well as
some bovine isolates from 1996 (this was one of
the only years we had disease in cattle caused by
BTV). Among the cattle isolates there are also
BTV 8 serotypes. We will be amplifying the
complete genomes shortly and sequencing selected
segments for comparison to the European strains.
If we can initiate cooperation, or if the BTV
strain from Europe is made available to our BTV
OIE Reference Centre, we can compare it to the S.A. isolates.
References:
(1) Potgieter A.C., Steele A. D., van Dijk A.A.
(2002). Cloning of complete genome sets of six
dsRNA viruses using an improved cloning method
for large dsRNA genes. J Gen Virol 2002 83(9): p. 2215-2223.
(2) Dungu B., Potgieter C., Von Teichman B.,
Smit.,T (2004). Vaccination in the control of
Bluetongue in Endemic Regions: The South African
Experience. Developments in Biologicals (Basel). 119:463-72
(3) A. C. Potgieter, F. Monaco, O. Mangana, K.
Nomikou, H. Yadin, G. Savini (2005). VP2-segment
Sequence Analysis of Some Isolates of Bluetongue
Virus Recovered in the Mediterranean Basin During
the 1998-2003 Outbreak. Journal of Veterinary
Medicine Series B 52 (9), 372-379.
--
Dr Christiaan Potgieter & Dr Truuske Gerdes
